Chapter 3

As the weeks went by, Simba faced more and more challenges in his role as king of the pride. A drought had settled over the savannah, and food was becoming scarce. Simba knew that he had to lead his pride to new hunting grounds, but the journey would be perilous, and many dangers lay ahead.

But Simba was determined to do whatever it took to protect his pride and ensure their survival. With the help of his most trusted advisors, he set out on a journey across the savannah, braving scorching temperatures, treacherous terrain, and fierce predators.
